      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/43721838-what-the-wind-knows">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5009669-tina?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5009669-tina?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5009669-tina?shelf=time-travel">time-travel</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2780072685" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer587714834910770622">This story was a superb 5 stars PLUS!<br/><br/>I listened to this book as an Audio and it was a beautiful, stunning story! I was mesmerized and enchanted by the setting and history of Ireland. The story was cleverly told in a unique way through time-travel and poetry. A timeless love story between Anne Gallagher and Thomas Smith!<br/><br/>I enjoyed the journey. Amy Harmon is definitely an author that I will automatically read again. This is one of the best books of 2019 in my opinion!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


