  <i>4.5 -5 Stars</i>
</b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1546550855i/26854175._SX540_.jpg' width='400' height='500' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Amy Harmon delivers a very well-researched/magical story doused in Irish history and a loop of souls that forever connect. You must read her ‘Author’s Note’ as she cleverly shows a correlation between her own family’s history mixed together with famous patriots of Ireland. <br/><br/>If you are a history buff, or a fan of fantastical love stories, or simply an Amy Harmon fan, then I think you will be as pleased as I was with Anne Gallagher’s story! <br/><br/><b>
  <i>&quot;I told you. You told me. Only the wind</i></b></span>
